# The canonical SovereignClaw oracle Dockerfile lives at the repo root
# (../../Dockerfile). Railway's builder refuses Dockerfiles nested under
# subdirs when the build context is the repo root, so we keep the real
# Dockerfile next to where the build context actually starts.
#
# Run a local dev container with:
#   docker build -f Dockerfile -t sovereignclaw-backend:dev .   # from repo root
#   docker compose -f apps/backend/docker-compose.yml up --build
#
# This stub exists so editors that "find Dockerfile near the app" still
# point you at the source of truth.
